<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,222,391]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,294,319]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Notes.</emphasis>
Polylectic, but prefers rosaceous plants in the genera 
<taxonomicName box="[915,1017,295,318]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Fragaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,1017,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fragaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(strawberry) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ribble 1968)" authorityName="Ribble" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Ribble" baseAuthorityYear="1968" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Potentilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1230,1341,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Potentilla</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ribble" firstAuthor="Ribble" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="237 - 394" refId="ref100263" refString="Ribble, D. W. (1968) Revisions of two subgenera of Andrena: Micrandrena Ashmead and Derandrena, new subgenus (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Bulletin of the University of Nebraska State Museum, 8, 237 - 394." type="journal article" year="1968">Ribble 1968</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This potential pollinator of strawberries can be collected in abundance from their flowers (
<bibRefCitation author="Knerer &amp; Atwood" firstAuthor="Knerer" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="41 - 56" refId="ref91726" refString="Knerer, G. &amp; Atwood, C. E. (1964 a) An annotated check list of the genus Andrena in Ontario (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Ontario, 94, 41 - 56." type="journal article" year="1964" yearSuffix="a">Knerer &amp; Atwood 1964a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
